  <residual_human_theory>

    <program_cannot_decide>
      which <trace> matters most;
      which <world> is ethically decisive;
      which <interpretation> carries the strongest historical force;
      when <intention> deserves mercy;
      when <consequence> overrides intention;
      when <technical_complexity> is real;
      when <technical_complexity> is an alibi;
      when <critique> becomes projection;
      when <responsibility> must be legally, morally, or historically assigned.
    </program_cannot_decide>

    <maintainer_warning>
      This is not a decoding machine.
      This is an interpretive discipline.

      It does not find hidden essence.
      It stages accountable reading.

      It does not abolish uncertainty.
      It makes uncertainty legible.

      It does not replace judgment.
      It forces judgment to name its evidence.
    </maintainer_warning>

  </residual_human_theory>


  <final_operator>
    <meaningful_action>
    [becomes
]
    <interpretable_text>
    WHEN
      <event> [vanishes
]
      AND <trace> [remains
]
      AND <trace> [opens
] <world>
      AND <world> [permits
] <rival_readings>
      AND <rival_readings> [undergo
] <validation>
      AND <validation> [preserves
] <residual_uncertainty>.
  </final_operator>

</PROGRAM_THEORY>